page.title: 14MID-SUSSEX HOUSING TYPES
page.content: {Medieval:}In our block,medieval style housing is very popular.As an old part of Sussex,it has houses ranging from the 16th century to today.{Great Walstead school}has a medieval house called {Walstead House} which was built in{1605}and is still in good condition. {Thatched:}Towards East Mascalls, (North of Great Walstead) there are 2 thatched houses.These are the only ones in our block. {Tythe Barns:}Tythe Barns are not very popular,but there quite a few. Great Walstead has one and there are others in the 11 farms in our block. { Modern Estates:}Scaynes Hill is the only populated town which has modern estates in our block.A lot of pensioners have council bungalows.Each house has good garden space.
